<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8"/>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <title>For Mama 🌸</title>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Libre+Baskerville:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&family=Lora:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;1,300;1,400&family=Sacramento&display=swap" rel="stylesheet"/>
  <style>
    *, *::before, *::after { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }

    :root {
      --bg:       #080d10;
      --bg2:      #0c1318;
      --gold:     #7ecac3;
      --gold-lt:  #a8e2dc;
      --rose:     #b07fa8;
      --cream:    #ddeae8;
      --muted:    #6a8a88;
      --white:    #f4faf9;
    }

    html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }

    body {
      background: var(--bg);
      color: var(--cream);
      font-family: 'Lora', serif;
      font-weight: 300;
      overflow-x: hidden;
      cursor: default;
    }

    /* ── NOISE GRAIN ── */
    body::after {
      content: '';
      position: fixed; inset: 0;
      background-image: url("data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg viewBox='0 0 256 256' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cfilter id='n'%3E%3CfeTurbulence type='fractalNoise' baseFrequency='0.9' numOctaves='4' stitchTiles='stitch'/%3E%3C/filter%3E%3Crect width='100%25' height='100%25' filter='url(%23n)' opacity='0.04'/%3E%3C/svg%3E");
      pointer-events: none;
      z-index: 999;
      opacity: 0.6;
    }

    /* ── SECTIONS ── */
    section {
      min-height: 100svh;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      padding: 80px 24px;
      position: relative;
    }

    /* ── SCROLL REVEAL ── */
    .reveal {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(36px);
      transition: opacity 0.9s ease, transform 0.9s ease;
    }
    .reveal.visible {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateY(0);
    }

    /* ════════════════════════
       §1  HERO
    ════════════════════════ */
    #hero {
      background: radial-gradient(ellipse at 50% 60%, #0d2a2e 0%, var(--bg) 70%);
      text-align: center;
      gap: 20px;
    }

    .hero-eyebrow {
      font-family: 'Lora', serif;
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.3em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--gold);
      opacity: 0;
      animation: fadeUp 1.2s ease forwards 0.2s;
    }

    .hero-title {
      font-family: 'Libre Baskerville', serif;
      font-size: clamp(3.2rem, 11vw, 8rem);
      font-weight: 700;
      line-height: 1;
      color: var(--white);
      opacity: 0;
      animation: fadeUp 1.2s ease forwards 0.6s;
    }
    .hero-title em {
      font-style: italic;
      color: var(--gold-lt);
    }

    .hero-script {
      font-family: 'Sacramento', cursive;
      font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 5vw, 2.8rem);
      color: var(--rose);
      opacity: 0;
      animation: fadeUp 1.2s ease forwards 1s;
    }

    .scroll-hint {
      position: absolute;
      bottom: 40px;
      left: 50%;
      transform: translateX(-50%);
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 8px;
      opacity: 0;
      animation: fadeUp 1s ease forwards 1.8s;
    }
    .scroll-hint span {
      font-size: 0.68rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.2em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--muted);
    }
    .scroll-line {
      width: 1px;
      height: 48px;
      background: linear-gradient(to bottom, var(--gold), transparent);
      animation: lineGrow 2s ease-in-out infinite;
    }
    @keyframes lineGrow {
      0%, 100% { transform: scaleY(1); opacity: 0.6; }
      50%       { transform: scaleY(1.3); opacity: 1; }
    }

    @keyframes fadeUp {
      from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(30px); }
      to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
    }

    /* ════════════════════════
       §2  COUNTER
    ════════════════════════ */
    #counter {
      background: var(--bg2);
      border-top: 1px solid #ffffff0a;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #ffffff0a;
      text-align: center;
      gap: 16px;
    }
    .counter-num {
      font-family: 'Libre Baskerville', serif;
      font-size: clamp(4rem, 18vw, 12rem);
      font-weight: 700;
      line-height: 1;
      color: var(--gold);
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    }
    .counter-label {
      font-size: clamp(0.8rem, 2vw, 1rem);
      letter-spacing: 0.28em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--muted);
    }
    .counter-sub {
      font-style: italic;
      font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.3rem);
      color: var(--cream);
      max-width: 520px;
      line-height: 1.7;
      margin-top: 8px;
    }

    /* ════════════════════════
       §3  LETTER
    ════════════════════════ */
    #letter {
      background: radial-gradient(ellipse at 30% 50%, #0a2a2866 0%, transparent 65%), var(--bg);
      align-items: flex-start;
    }

    .letter-wrap {
      max-width: 660px;
      width: 100%;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .letter-tag {
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.3em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--gold);
      margin-bottom: 32px;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 12px;
    }
    .letter-tag::after {
      content: '';
      flex: 1;
      height: 1px;
      background: linear-gradient(to right, var(--gold), transparent);
      max-width: 120px;
    }

    .letter-body {
      font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 2.2vw, 1.22rem);
      line-height: 2;
      color: #d4c4b4;
      font-style: italic;
    }
    .letter-body p + p { margin-top: 1.4em; }
    .letter-body strong {
      font-style: normal;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--gold-lt);
    }

    .letter-sign {
      margin-top: 48px;
      font-family: 'Sacramento', cursive;
      font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 5vw, 2.4rem);
      color: var(--rose);
      text-align: right;
    }

    /* photo placeholder */
    .photo-slot {
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 420px;
      aspect-ratio: 4/5;
      margin: 0 auto 48px;
      border-radius: 4px;
      overflow: hidden;
      position: relative;
      border: 1px solid #ffffff11;
    }
    .photo-slot img {
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      object-fit: cover;
      filter: sepia(0.3) brightness(0.9);
    }
    .photo-slot .photo-placeholder {
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #080f12, #0f2028);
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      gap: 12px;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.2em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }
    .photo-slot .photo-placeholder span { font-size: 2rem; }

    /* ════════════════════════
       §4  REASONS
    ════════════════════════ */
    #reasons {
      background: var(--bg2);
      align-items: center;
    }

    .reasons-header {
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 64px;
    }
    .reasons-header h2 {
      font-family: 'Libre Baskerville', serif;
      font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 4vw, 2.6rem);
      font-weight: 400;
      font-style: italic;
      color: var(--white);
    }
    .reasons-header p {
      margin-top: 10px;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.2em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--gold);
    }

    .reasons-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
      gap: 1px;
      max-width: 900px;
      width: 100%;
      background: #ffffff08;
      border: 1px solid #ffffff08;
      border-radius: 2px;
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    .reason-item {
      padding: 36px 32px;
      background: var(--bg2);
      transition: background 0.4s ease;
      position: relative;
    }
    .reason-item:hover { background: #0c1e22; }

    .reason-num {
      font-family: 'Libre Baskerville', serif;
      font-size: 0.7rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.2em;
      color: var(--gold);
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
    .reason-text {
      font-size: clamp(0.95rem, 1.8vw, 1.05rem);
      line-height: 1.8;
      color: #c4b4a4;
    }
    .reason-text strong {
      color: var(--white);
      font-weight: 700;
    }

    /* ════════════════════════
       §5  CLOSING
    ════════════════════════ */
    #closing {
      background: radial-gradient(ellipse at 60% 40%, #0d2a30 0%, var(--bg) 65%);
      text-align: center;
      gap: 24px;
    }

    .closing-icon {
      font-size: 2.8rem;
      animation: heartbeat 2.2s ease-in-out infinite;
    }
    @keyframes heartbeat {
      0%, 100% { transform: scale(1); }
      14%       { transform: scale(1.18); }
      28%       { transform: scale(1); }
      42%       { transform: scale(1.12); }
      56%       { transform: scale(1); }
    }

    .closing-title {
      font-family: 'Libre Baskerville', serif;
      font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 6vw, 3.6rem);
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--white);
      line-height: 1.15;
    }
    .closing-title em {
      font-style: italic;
      color: var(--gold-lt);
    }

    .closing-body {
      max-width: 520px;
      font-size: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.18rem);
      line-height: 1.9;
      color: #b0a090;
      font-style: italic;
    }

    .closing-sign {
      font-family: 'Sacramento', cursive;
      font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 6vw, 3rem);
      color: var(--rose);
      margin-top: 8px;
    }

    .divider-line {
      width: 60px;
      height: 1px;
      background: linear-gradient(to right, transparent, var(--gold), transparent);
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    /* ── RESPONSIVE ── */
    @media (max-width: 600px) {
      .reasons-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      section { padding: 60px 20px; }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- ══ §1 HERO ══ -->
<section id="hero">
  <p class="hero-eyebrow">A Mother's Day tribute · 2026</p>
  <h1 class="hero-title">Happy<br/><em>Mother's</em><br/>Day.</h1>
  <p class="hero-script">For the woman who is home.</p>
  <div class="scroll-hint">
    <span>Read on</span>
    <div class="scroll-line"></div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ══ §2 COUNTER ══ -->
<section id="counter">
  <div class="reveal">
    <p class="counter-label">A lifetime of love</p>
    <p class="counter-num">∞</p>
    <p class="counter-sub">
      No number is big enough. No words are wide enough.<br/>
      But we try anyway — because you deserve it.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ══ §3 LETTER ══ -->
<section id="letter">
  <div class="letter-wrap">

    <div class="photo-slot reveal">
      <!-- Drop your photo here: replace the div below with <img src="your-photo.jpg" alt="Mama"/> -->
      <img src="mama.jpg" alt="Mama"/>
        <span>🌸</span>
        Place her photo here
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="letter-tag reveal">A letter from the heart</div>

    <div class="letter-body reveal">
      <p>Dear Mama,</p>

      <p>
        There is a kind of love that doesn't announce itself — it just
        <strong>shows up</strong>. In the early mornings before anyone else was awake.
        In the meals made without being asked. In the way you always seemed to
        know, even when I said nothing at all.
      </p>

      <p>
        You have given me more than I can count and more than I will ever
        fully understand. You gave me <strong>a sense of home</strong> that I carry
        everywhere I go — into every room, every challenge, every dream I dare
        to chase.
      </p>

      <p>
        I know I don't always say it the way I should. But today, on this day,
        I want you to know: <strong>everything good in me points back to you</strong>.
        The patience. The warmth. The refusal to give up. All you.
      </p>

      <p>
        Thank you for being exactly who you are — not just my mother,
        but the person I look up to most in this world.
      </p>

      <p>Happy Mother's Day. 🌸</p>
    </div>

    <p class="letter-sign reveal">— With all my love, Fredrick Oindo 🖤</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ══ §4 REASONS ══ -->
<section id="reasons">
  <div class="reasons-header reveal">
    <p>Why you matter to me.</p>
    <h2>Six things I never say enough.</h2>
  </div>

  <div class="reasons-grid">
    <div class="reason-item reveal">
      <p class="reason-num">01</p>
      <p class="reason-text">Because you taught me that <strong>strength doesn't shout</strong> — it quietly keeps going, day after day, without asking for applause.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="reason-item reveal">
      <p class="reason-num">02</p>
      <p class="reason-text">Because your laugh is the <strong>most comfortable sound</strong> in the world to me. Nothing else comes close.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="reason-item reveal">
      <p class="reason-num">03</p>
      <p class="reason-text">Because you believed in me <strong>before I believed in myself</strong> — and that belief became the ground I stand on.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="reason-item reveal">
      <p class="reason-num">04</p>
      <p class="reason-text">Because on the hardest days, knowing you exist in this world <strong>makes it easier</strong> to keep going.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="reason-item reveal">
      <p class="reason-num">05</p>
      <p class="reason-text">Because the sacrifices you made quietly, without ceremony — I see them. I <strong>always saw them</strong>. Thank you.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="reason-item reveal">
      <p class="reason-num">06</p>
      <p class="reason-text">Because being your child is the one thing I'd never trade — not for anything, <strong>not for the world</strong>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ══ §5 CLOSING ══ -->
<section id="closing">
  <div class="reveal closing-icon">🌸</div>
  <div class="divider-line reveal"></div>
  <h2 class="closing-title reveal">Here's to you,<br/><em>always.</em></h2>
  <p class="closing-body reveal">
    May today feel as warm as the love you've poured into a lifetime of
    being there. You are not just celebrated today — you are cherished,
    always.
  </p>
  <p class="closing-sign reveal">Happy Mother's Day, Mama 💛</p>
</section>

<script>
  // Scroll reveal
  const reveals = document.querySelectorAll('.reveal');
  const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
    entries.forEach(e => {
      if (e.isIntersecting) {
        e.target.classList.add('visible');
        observer.unobserve(e.target);
      }
    });
  }, { threshold: 0.15 });
  reveals.forEach(el => observer.observe(el));
</script>

</body>
</html>
